10/10/2025, 19:33 - +91 97114 64682: If the fixed bin is full, it does not check for random empty bins in between. 
Instead, it looks for the bin with the highest "Bin Ranking" within the same warehouse zone that has capacity and  is valid for 
put-away.

Identify all the bins you would be willing to use for storing Item A.

In the Bin Creation worksheet or the Bin List, assign them a Bin Ranking.
    001-C (Fixed Bin): Ranking = 10 (Highest)
   001-B: Ranking = 9
   001-D: Ranking = 8
   009-M (Replenishment):Ranking = 7
   ...and so on.

 Ensure all these bins are in the same Zone and that the zone is set up for the correct put-away and pick activities.

Result: When 001-C is full, the system will automatically direct the overflow to bin 001-B (Rank 9). If that is full, it will go to 001-D (Rank 8), and only if all higher-ranked bins are full will it finally use 009-M (Rank 7).
